Only the last one is complicated. Writing it as a quadratic in <M>u</M>  we have  <M>u^2-(4v)u+4v^2-v\leq 0.</M>  The
 roots of the corresponding
 equation are <M>r_1, r_2</M> 
 where
<D>r_1 = 2v-\sqrt v < r_2 = 2v+\sqrt v.</D>
So we must have <M>r_1 \leq u \leq r_2.</M>  Since <M>v\geq 0,</M>  and <M>r_1 < 0,</M>  hence we have <M>0\leq v\leq r_2.</M> 
-------EOD-------
